Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.66,0:00:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must say, sir, that you have laid \N eyes on a fine piece of property.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.49,0:00:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The best thing about this place is that it is only \N twenty minutes from the center of Berlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.94,0:00:11.82,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,88)\pos(319,285)}Berlin \N (Old East Germany Side)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, it has fine transportation facilities \N and is in an excellent location.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.04,0:00:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never find another estate quite \N like this in old East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.92,0:00:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.97,0:00:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe this is East German Trade \N Adviser Liebert's former house...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.64,0:00:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.19,0:00:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?  You only came here to inquire about Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.23,0:00:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were a customer...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.36,0:00:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is something I have to know, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.82,0:00:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything about the government \N official who passed away ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.78,0:00:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Lieberts took twins into custody when they lived here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.58,0:00:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.08,0:00:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the man who owns this place...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.75,0:00:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you introduce me to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.54,0:00:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.75,0:01:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the old East\NGerman properties belong to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.54,0:01:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the wealthy Jews who\Nfled during the Nazi regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.14,0:01:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Eastern government is paying foreign countries \N as well as the West to rent the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.68,0:01:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place's owner also resides in another country.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.02,0:01:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.27,0:01:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our real estate company in the West \N expanded after the wall fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.82,0:01:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we don't know anything about the old tales!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.53,0:01:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm locking the gate now, so please leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.91,0:01:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone know what happened ten years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.24,0:01:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would anyone remember Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.91,0:01:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I told you earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.25,0:01:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this was the residential district of the \N former top government officials.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.79,0:01:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once the wall fell, most of them fled for their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.34,0:01:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who worked in the Ministry of Domestic Affairs \N were especially threatened...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.55,0:01:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, now that I think about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.51,0:01:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be a former East German Department of \N Commerce official living ten houses down from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.18,0:01:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.39,0:01:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't need to risk his life the way he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.23,0:01:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he only had waited a little longer, East \N Germany would have destroyed itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.23,0:02:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand why he went to \N the country of freedom, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.20,0:02:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was even murdered...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.03,0:02:10.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Mr. Liebert have twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.87,0:02:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Twins...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.46,0:02:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.54,0:02:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The twins Mr. Liebert adopted from the orphanage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.67,0:02:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.88,0:02:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were such cute children...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.59,0:02:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Liebert always wanted children of his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.72,0:02:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Where is this orphanage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I think it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.27,0:02:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,511...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.31,0:02:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.90,0:02:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.23,0:02:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinderheim... 511...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.53,0:05:14.66,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,113)\pos(319,320)}Kinderheim 511
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place used to be an orphanage, \N but soon it will be a supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.54,0:05:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel so relieved knowing that this disturbing \N building will finally be torn down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.04,0:05:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.00,0:05:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where I can find the orphanage employees?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.01,0:05:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Employees...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any left, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.34,0:05:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to discuss this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.66,0:05:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, this place gives me the chills!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.66,0:05:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,E-Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you really want to hear about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.27,0:06:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a man named Hartmann who used to work \N in the Ministry of Health lives in No. 47.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.50,0:06:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, does a man named Hartmann live around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.51,0:06:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.64,0:06:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are injured!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.89,0:06:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is alright.  Don't be scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.73,0:06:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got hurt in a place that was still healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.15,0:06:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's festering.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.11,0:06:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bear with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.15,0:06:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It stings a little, but this will help you get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.66,0:06:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, you are all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.21,0:07:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't trip now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.00,0:07:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will get hurt again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.09,0:07:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hartmann...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.53,0:07:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I took all those children in and became their \N foster parent after the wall came down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.83,0:07:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Foster parent...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.96,0:07:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.  I raised those children until they were adopted or could live on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The child in the middle was adopted by the president \N of a company that makes clothing and accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.43,0:07:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The child on the left is currently in the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.68,0:07:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking care of one right now, as a matter of fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.14,0:07:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.93,0:08:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if I would call it work or what...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.90,0:08:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was a government official and in charge of the Ministry of \N Health and Welfare in this district for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.36,0:08:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and I worked with the orphanage a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.48,0:08:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been against the government since that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.37,0:08:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since socialism collapsed, I thought \N I could help the children in my own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.79,0:08:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I'm poor, though, it is not going as I had planned...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, they are still much better off \N than when they were in the orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.96,0:08:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinderheim 511 was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a special orphanage under the cooperative jurisdiction...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.74,0:08:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...of the Ministry of Health and Welfare \N and the Ministry of Home Affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.76,0:08:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the orphanages of the Old East \N Germany were mostly like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.27,0:08:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amongst them, the special orphanages were the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.36,0:08:50.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't just a facility for children \N who didn't have a place to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.86,0:08:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a collection of children with criminal records...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.61,0:08:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...children of parents who committed political \N crimes when they tried to escape...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.08,0:09:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and children of parents were charged \N with rebellion or espionage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.33,0:09:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why they were subjected to discrimination \N and treated inhumanely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.96,0:09:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The children couldn't fight back, no matter what was inflicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.80,0:09:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That place was the very contradiction \N of socialism and totalitarianism!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.39,0:09:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In their propaganda, the government said...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.35,0:09:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that they would re-educate the children \N to become the models of socialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.60,0:09:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in reality, they treated them like criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.15,0:09:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, the director and educators were horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.36,0:09:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the worst would even confiscate and \N sell packages sent to the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.87,0:09:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder who the real criminals were...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.29,0:09:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fear and violence controlled the special orphanages...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.04,0:09:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was impossible to raise a normal person there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.88,0:09:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then... that incident occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.13,0:09:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.01,0:09:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened at that orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.47,0:10:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you wanted to ask me about those twins, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.22,0:10:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know something about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.31,0:10:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know much about the sister, since she was \N placed in an orphanage in another district.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.15,0:10:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.52,0:10:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I know a good deal about her brother, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.40,0:10:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.28,0:10:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is right!  I want to ask you about Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.79,0:10:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.91,0:10:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was top secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.88,0:10:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The government of East Germany \N issued a gag order regarding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.09,0:10:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, it is all in the past now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.88,0:10:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I don't think it would matter it I \N talked about the incident, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.60,0:10:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.64,0:10:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.97,0:10:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did Johan do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.52,0:10:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He led an uprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.95,0:10:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.45,0:11:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Dieter. We have a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.49,0:11:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.37,0:11:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is with that attitude, Dieter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.64,0:11:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Greet him properly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.52,0:11:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.83,0:11:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We met in front of the house earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.63,0:11:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.71,0:11:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, about what we were just talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.51,0:11:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, I don't want to discuss that in front of the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.97,0:11:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you are right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.64,0:11:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is getting late, so I will stop by again some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.94,0:11:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dieter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.11,0:11:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to have dinner with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.61,0:11:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.02,0:11:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tenma, since you are a freelance journalist...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.89,0:11:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you are going to write an article about \N the things you are researching, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.36,0:11:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.15,0:11:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then please make sure you write down this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.22,0:12:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The growth of a child depends entirely \N on the adult raising him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.18,0:12:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must lead our children down the right path.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.85,0:12:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, for the first time, the children \N can have wonderful dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.57,0:12:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dreams, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.32,0:12:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of dreams do you have, Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.53,0:12:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A soccer ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.99,0:12:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.45,0:12:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want a soccer ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.04,0:12:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.25,0:12:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.98,0:12:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to continue our conversation \N at another time, if you don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.59,0:12:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.59,0:12:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our conversation was interrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.34,0:12:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stop by again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.72,0:12:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll contact you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.84,0:12:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dieter...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.56,0:13:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.99,0:13:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mind if I take a look around?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.02,0:13:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.48,0:13:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.57,0:13:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hartmann.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.11,0:13:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.20,0:13:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is wrong, Mr. Hartmann?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.83,0:13:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.70,0:13:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.83,0:14:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.88,0:14:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.08,0:14:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.84,0:14:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was on the chair, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.21,0:14:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Dieter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.92,0:14:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts... it hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.93,0:14:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where does it hurt, Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.64,0:14:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.64,0:14:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hartmann, call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.35,0:14:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.06,0:14:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me take a look, Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.65,0:14:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are all these bruises?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.78,0:14:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.49,0:14:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it hurt here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.36,0:14:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's broken two of his ribs...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.45,0:14:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.12,0:14:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he's dislocated his left shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.25,0:14:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can all of this occur from falling off a chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.52,0:14:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ambulance will be here shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.90,0:14:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So everything should be alright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.38,0:14:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.76,0:14:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what are these injuries from?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.63,0:14:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said everything is okay now, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.63,0:14:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So please leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.59,0:14:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.55,0:14:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.10,0:15:00.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the way you touch the injuries...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.81,0:15:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is as if you are a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.68,0:15:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.92,0:15:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.17,0:15:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder that name sounded familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.40,0:15:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a doctor, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.19,0:15:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one wanted for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.66,0:15:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These injuries...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.45,0:15:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did he get all these injuries?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.20,0:15:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, Mr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.45,0:15:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think you should start running?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.52,0:15:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I called the police along with an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.96,0:15:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.13,0:15:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you how Dieter got these injuries!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.59,0:15:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter to a murderer and a fugitive \N like yourself, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.35,0:15:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I expect nothing less from a fugitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.23,0:15:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a short temper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.62,0:15:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did this to him, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.56,0:15:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did... what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.73,0:15:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are abusing Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.24,0:15:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Abusing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.49,0:15:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you would not phrase it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.53,0:16:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.33,0:16:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you planning to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.17,0:16:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking him to a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.50,0:16:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First murder, now kidnapping?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.50,0:16:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.42,0:16:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know you will be caught quickly if you do that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.02,0:16:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Dieter!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.31,0:16:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking you to a hospital now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.31,0:16:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared... of hospitals...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.15,0:16:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing to be scared of.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.61,0:16:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The doctors will help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.94,0:16:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hartmann always... treats the pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.29,0:16:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you are hurt all over...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.12,0:16:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you haven't been to a hospital?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.25,0:16:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world is full of bad things...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.73,0:16:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why I have to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.86,0:17:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to be strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.34,0:17:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Mr. Hartmann tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world is in an abyss...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.85,0:17:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.44,0:17:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That the world is in an abyss is the biggest lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.53,0:17:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.86,0:17:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.53,0:17:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.47,0:17:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, I got you a soccer ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.37,0:17:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow will definitely be a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.05,0:17:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for asking, this late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.76,0:17:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is fine, but we are bogged down with emergency \N cases, so it will take some time to treat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.60,0:17:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, can't you do something about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.60,0:17:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there was a really big accident, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.70,0:17:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bus driver died instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.85,0:17:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We would like to ask the truck driver about the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.52,0:17:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can still talk even with both feet broken, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.44,0:17:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His treatment comes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.48,0:18:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please conduct the investigation later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.07,0:18:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we will wait right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.11,0:18:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will be back in about two hours.  \N  Then we will wait right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.87,0:18:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will be back in about two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.12,0:18:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take care of that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.50,0:18:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, if someone other than myself \N comes to pick up the boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.79,0:18:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...don't release him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.17,0:18:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.86,0:18:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.72,0:18:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the scene of the accident all cleared up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.47,0:18:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it is still congested.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.35,0:18:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.85,0:18:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...what should I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.68,0:18:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I have to find a place for Dieter to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.48,0:18:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I turned him over to the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.56,0:18:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I can't go with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.82,0:18:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know much...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.30,0:18:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...about the sister, since she was placed \N in an orphanage in another district.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.16,0:18:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.79,0:18:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.00,0:19:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a child you want us to take in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.26,0:19:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.34,0:19:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you come at such a late hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.97,0:19:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what I'm asking is absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.22,0:19:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that child is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.10,0:19:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that he is being abused.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.19,0:19:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if I don't who you are, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.94,0:19:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, that is ...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.98,0:19:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't take in a child from someone we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.40,0:19:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,E-Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.99,0:19:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But could this be the orphanage Anna Liebert attended?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.49,0:19:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.75,0:19:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.79,0:19:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-So Anna was here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.67,0:19:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it brings back so many memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.17,0:19:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is Anna doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.76,0:19:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.26,0:19:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.51,0:19:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is currently attending Heidelberg College.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.35,0:19:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.22,0:19:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she found happiness!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.27,0:19:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna was such a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.35,0:19:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew her only until she was taken in \N by Foreign Trade Adviser Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.27,0:20:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Along with her brother, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.50,0:20:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, what was his name...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.01,0:20:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.07,0:20:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.41,0:20:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two got along very well, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.66,0:20:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...they were sent to two different \N orphanages.  I felt sorry for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.41,0:20:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before the came here, they really were alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.96,0:20:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when they were found near \N the border of Czechoslovakia...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.96,0:20:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I heard they were walking together, hand in hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.63,0:20:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both shivering from the cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.43,0:20:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Mr. Liebert said he was going to take in a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.64,0:20:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it was only being to be Johan at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.60,0:20:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Johan would only go if his sister was with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.81,0:20:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to him, Anna was able to find happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.73,0:20:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the orphanages in East Germany \N were horrible at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.95,0:20:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't compare us to Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.84,0:21:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inge, that is not the way to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.59,0:21:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.89,0:21:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.76,0:21:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.  It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.89,0:21:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing to be scared of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.23,0:21:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, you can go to the bathroom by yourself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.49,0:21:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These children don't know the love of their true parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.82,0:21:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need love in order to mature as a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.91,0:21:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you said, the orphanages in East \N Germany at the time were terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.79,0:21:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place used to be called Orphanage No. 47, as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.13,0:21:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, we still tried our best \N to make something happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.97,0:21:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tried to go against the government, even slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.14,0:21:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we wouldn't turn out to be like Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.31,0:22:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That place was a special orphanage \N under the cooperative jurisdiction...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.12,0:22:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...of the Ministry of Health and Welfare \N and the Ministry of Home Affairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.27,0:22:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.78,0:22:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the internal conditions were monitored \N by the Ministry of Domestic Affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.57,0:22:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because that place was old East Germany's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.58,0:22:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...testing facility.
